Package musicRepresentation

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SoundUnit
    The SoundUnit interface is implemented by the Rest and Chord class.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ABCHeader
    This class stores basic information about an .abc music.
    ABCHeaderTest  
    ABCMusic
    This class consists of a representation of an .abc file, in a way that is possible to extract information to be played with some kind of sequencer.
    ABCMusicParseListener  
    ABCMusicParseListenerTest
    Test suite for the ABCMusic parser.
    ABCMusicTest
    Test suite for the ABCMusic class.
    Chord
    The Chord class implements the SoundUnit class.
    ChordTest  
    KeySignature
    Represents accidentals as a Map in a key signature.
    KeySignatureTest  
    Measure
    Represents a Measure.
    MeasureTest
    This is the test suite for the Measure class.
    MidiNoteRepresentation
    Represents a note that can be interpreted as a MIDI note.
    MidiNoteRepresentationTest
    MidiNoteRepresentation tests.
    Note
    The Note class is composed of a Pitch object and a durationMultiplier (defaults to 1).
    NoteTest
    This is the test suite for the Note class.
    Rest
    The Rest class implements SoundUnit along with the Chord class.
    RestTest  
    SequencerInformation
    Immutable class that has music information for the SequencePlayer.
    SequencerInformationTest
    Test suite for SequencerInformation class.
    Syllable
    This class represents a syllable to be shown by the karaoke and also the time when it occurs in the music that it belongs to.
    SyllableTest
    Test suite for Syllable class.
    Voice
    The Voice class represents a Voice in an abc music file.
    VoiceTest
